Diagnosis:
Scutum rectangular (
Fig. 54D
). Ocularium on the anterior margin of prosoma, elevated, blunt and smooth, without eyes (
Fig. 54B
). Clear lateral areas projected in digitiform tubercles, clear area on apex of dorsal area V forming a large, rounded tubercle (
Fig. 54A, D
). Basichelicera elongated. Lacking ornamentation on the dorsum and legs. Femur IV noticeably longer than scutum. Male genitalia: pars distalis slightly swollen in the middle, ventral plate a little compressed in lateral view, apical margin convex. Four pairs of lateral setae, cylindrical and shorter than width of pars distalis. Four pairs of ventral microsetae along lateral margins of pars distalis, basal pair separated from the rest. Two pairs of parastylar setae, lateral projection of follis lobate, rounded distally (
Fig. 55
).
